This application is not packaged and must be run from this source tree.
Requires Inkscape & zenity applications and pySVG python library

***** For Linux *****

1. Get packaged software dependencies:

sudo apt-get install inkscape
sudo apt-get install zenity

2. == Get unpackaged pySVG python library ==

From this page:

http://code.google.com/p/pysvg/downloads/list

Download the file pysvg-0.2.1.zip

Unzip it and install it:

$ unzip pysvg-0.2.1.zip
$ cd pysvg-0.2.1/
$ sudo python setup.py install

3. == Get the tmtp source code ==

To get the source, do the following:

$ git clone git@github.com:sconklin/tmtp.git

4. == Test it ==

$ cd ../tmtp/standalone
$ ./mkpattern --verbose --client=customer/SampleClient/SampleClient.json --pattern=patterns/SamplePattern.py --styles=tmtp_styles.json foo.svg

If this completes without error, everything is probably good.
You can look at the output file, foo.svg to see what it looks like

$ inkscape --file=foo.svg --verb=ZoomPage --select=A.cuttingline --select=B.cuttingline --verb=SelectionOffset --verb=FileSave

NOTE: To print: In inkscape, hide the reference layer, arrange pattern pieces for best use of space
for plotter/printer size. Resize document to fit using appropriate border size, save as PDF, and print.

5. == Update the tmtp.sh script ==

$ gedit tmtp.sh

change TMTP_BASE to your tmtp/standalone directory, example:
	TMTP_BASE=/home/susan/src/tmtp/standalone/

6. == Test the script ==

$ ./tmtp.sh

7. == Update launcher desktop file ==

$ sudo gedit tmtp.desktop

Edit directories for icon and executable to your tmtp/standalone directory

8. == Add TMTP script to desktop Launcher bar ==

$ sudo cp tmtp.destop /usr/share/applications
$ sudo chmod +x /usr/share/applications/tmtp.desktop
$ sudo update-desktop-database

Click on Ubuntu logo at top of desktop Launcher bar
type in tmtp.desktop to find file icon
drag file icon to Launcher bar

The Scissors icon should appear in Launcher



